    "text": "JOHANNESBURG, April 3 (Reuters) - The Modikwa platinum mine in South Africa has halted production after six workers en route to the operation were burnt to death in a petrol bomb attack on a bus, a spokeswoman for African Rainbow Minerals (ARM) said on Tuesday.\nThe mine in north east South Africa is operated by ARM and Anglo American Platinum. (Reporting by Ed Stoddard, editing by Louise Heavens)\n ",
